<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-80-0364 </DOCNO><TEXT>Lead-acid batteries are today used mainly in the field of industrial vehicles,in addition also in industrial appliances, for instance road sweepingmachines. Among the rail vehicles: shunting engines of private railways,mining locomotives, battery jennys of monorail suspension railways andthe storage battery rail cars of the German Federal Railway. Lead-acidbatteries are also used in boats and ships in various types. Whilst theafore-mentioned modes of use are established market areas for lead-acidbatteries, the field of electric transport vehicles has remained untiltoday a proving ground for improved battery construction - this for omnibuses,transporters and private cars. (orig./GG)</TEXT></DOC>